  "prompt": "Does cctv works during power cut?",
  "response": "Whether CCTV cameras work during a power cut depends on their power source and configuration. Here are some common scenarios:\n\n1. **Battery-Operated Cameras**: Some CCTV systems use rechargeable or replaceable batteries, allowing them to function during a power cut.\n\n2. **Uninterruptible Power Supplies (UPS)**: Many surveillance systems can be connected to a UPS, which provides backup power during outages. This setup can keep the cameras and recording devices operational until the power is restored.\n\n3. **Solar-Powered Cameras**: Some modern CCTV systems are solar-powered, meaning they can operate independently of the grid, making them effective during power outages.\n\n4. **Wired Systems**: Traditional wired CCTV systems that do not have a backup power solution will not function during a power cut, as they rely on electricity from the mains.\n\n5. **Network-Connected Cameras**: For IP cameras that rely on local Wi-Fi networks, a power loss may affect not just the camera but also the network equipment (like routers) and recording devices if they are not on backup power.\n\nIn summary, to ensure CCTV cameras work during power outages, it\u2019s advisable to incorporate battery backups, UPS systems, or select battery-operated or solar-powered options.",
